        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 6 at 8:00PM EDT by NWS Raleigh NC</headline>
        <description>At 800 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms along a line extending from Dahlia to near Ebony.
Movement was southeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Roanoke Rapids, Halifax, Littleton, Enfield, Weldon, South Weldon,
Rosemary, Lake Gaston, Southpointe And Morningstar Marinas, and
Roanoke Rapids Lake.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
